HEADWORD: Engore
<hw>En*gore"</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>v. t.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>To
gore; to pierce; to lacerate.</def> <mark>[Obs.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Deadly <qex>engored</qex> of a great wild boar.</q>
<rj><qau>Spenser.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>To make bloody.</def> <mark>[Obs.]</mark>
<rj><au>Chapman.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Engorge</ent>⟦br⟧
